		"description": "<p>The head of this warhammer appears as a wooden keg used for storing beer, and when swung, sloshing liquid can be heard inside. However, it is abnormally strong and does not break on impact. This weapon grants a +3 to attack and damage rolls made with it.</p>\n<p>The keg hammer has 8 charges. When you make an attack roll with this hammer, you may expend 2 charges to release some of its pent-up carbonation to increase the velocity of your swing, dealing an extra 3d8 force damage on a hit. The keg hammer regains 1d6 charges each dawn.</p>",
